http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/andhra-pradesh/70-year-old-dies-after-being-hit-by-car/article13978730.ece

A man attempted to flee after hitting a 70-year-old pedestrian while the latter lie dead on his car.The accused, Raheem Khan, and his friend Shabad Khan, were proceeding towards Vijayawada from Hyderabad, when they hit Komirelly Venkat Reddy, native of Narketpally on NH-65 bypass road. Venkat Reddy sustained multiple injuries and died on the spot. In a bid to escape from the scene, Raheem Khan drove the car a few kilometres away carrying the body on his car. While the locals alleged that the duo attempted to dump the body on the roadside near Kattangur, the accused told the police that he was taking the victim to a hospital. When asked why he did not shift the body inside the car, he had no answer. A case was registered.